messages.content: ComfyUI-SSREncoder is a ComfyUI node that utilizes the SSR Encoder models for alignment and attentions in image generation.
Where can I find the SSR Encoder models for ComfyUI-SSREncoder?
The SSR Encoder models for ComfyUI-SSREncoder can be found on Huggingface at https://huggingface.co/logtd/ssr_encoder/tree/main.
Where should I download the SSR Encoder models for ComfyUI-SSREncoder?
Download the SSR Encoder models to your `ComfyUI/models/ssr` directory.
Are there any example workflows available for ComfyUI-SSREncoder?
Yes, you can find example workflows for ComfyUI-SSREncoder in the `example_workflows` directory of the repository.
What does the example image 'example_ssr_one' demonstrate?
The 'example_ssr_one' image demonstrates an example output generated using the ComfyUI-SSREncoder node, showcasing its capabilities in image generation with SSR Encoder models.
The 'wolf_woman_example_ssr' image shows another example output generated using the ComfyUI-SSREncoder node, featuring a wolf woman character.
How can I access the example images for ComfyUI-SSREncoder?

You can access the example images for ComfyUI-SSREncoder by visiting the provided GitHub URLs: https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/62f5725b-040d-483f-87f3-ae1bbf123e59 for 'example_ssr_one' and https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/59750e57-abab-412d-abe5-cc09b1c28ea3 for 'wolf_woman_example_ssr'.
